'''''Star Wars Insider'' 71''' is the seventy-first issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was released to newsstands in [[October]] [[2003]]. The subscriber-exclusive edition of issue 71 included the fifth volume of ''[[Bantha Tracks (department)|Bantha Tracks]]'', the [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Official ''Star Wars'' Fan Club]] newsletter.

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"From the Editor's Desk"
*"[[Rebel Rumblings]]"
*"[[Star News]]" {{C|by [[Lisa Spencer]], [[Benjamin Harper]]}}
*"[[Best of Hyperspace]]" {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]] and [[Paul Ens]]}}
*"[[HoloNet News (Insider)|HoloNet News]]" {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]]}}
**"[[Republic HoloNet News Core Edition 14:10:03]]"
**"[[CIS Shadowfeed Dispatch 14:10:05 Edition]]"
*"[[Gamescape]]" &mdash; The ''Star Wars'' Galaxies Gazetteer {{C|by [[W. Haden Blackman]]}}
*"[[Set Piece]]" &mdash; Anakin's Hovel {{C|by [[Chris Trevas]]}}
*"[[Bookshelf]]" &mdash; A Race to The Finish{{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*"[[Comics Link]]" &mdash; Forget What You Know {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" &mdash; A Burning Question: To 'Ruin' a Collectible or Not? {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet|Steve Sansweet]]}}
*"[[Toy Box]]" &mdash; These ARE the Jedi Master Points You're Looking For! {{C|by Andy@Hasbro}}
*"[[Crossword (department)|Crossword]]" &mdash; More Songs of the Mos Eisley Cantina {{C|by [[Michael Selinker]]}}
*"[[Star Wars Q&A|''Star Wars'' Q&A'']] {{C|by Pablo Hidalgo}}
*"[[The Last Page]]" {{C|by [[Tony Moseley]]}}

===Features===
*"[[Prequel Update]]"
*:<small>[[Rick McCallum|Rick's]] too busy to talk much this month-instead he sent these fabulous photos.</small>
*"[[Insider's Holiday Gift Guide|''Insider's'' Holiday Gift Guide]]" by [[Victor Wertz|Vic Wertz]]
*:<small>Our second annual list of suggestions for what to buy ''[[Star Wars]]'' fans who have everything.</small>
*"[[A Visit to Rancho Obi-Wan]]" {{C|by [[Justin Lambros]]}}
*:<small>Take an exclusive tour through one of the world's most fabulous collections: [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]'s own ''[[Star Wars]]'' museum.</small>
*"[[A Fistful of Credits: The Star Wars Insider Collector's Spending Spree Challenge|A Fistful of Credits: The ''Star Wars Insider'' Collector's Spending Spree Challenge]]" {{C|by [[Pete Vilmur]]}}
*:<small>Five collecting teams go in ... and all five come out with the best collectibles $100 can buy.</small>
*"[[Some Assembly Required: A Short History of Star Wars Model Kits|Some Assembly Required: A Short History of ''Star Wars'' Model Kits]]" {{C|by [[Jay Chladek]]}}
*:<small>Sometimes the best collectibles you have to build yourself.</small>
*"Museum Pieces: The Adventures of ''Indiana Jones'' Finally Come to DVD" by [[Dave Gross]]
*:<small>At last, the [[Indiana Jones]] movies are available on DVD. Here's how digital restoration and documentary filmmaking helped them get there.</small>
*"Keep It Moving" by [[Ron Magid]]
*:<small>Veteran model maker Lorne Peterson recalls the challenges and triumphs of creating visual effects for the adventures of Indiana Jones.</small>
*"[[Hero: Harrison Ford on Playing Heroes, Handling the Paparazzi and Returning as Indiana Jones]]" by [[Gabriela Tscharner-Patao]]
*:<small>While [[Harrison Ford]] is ready for a few laughs, he's still primed to don the hat and crack the whip one more time.</small>

